Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g}(diced), @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and onion and stir-fry until golden, ~{6-7%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook bacon thoroughly. Add the garlic and @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} and stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Stir the @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1%carton}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @Worcester sauce{15%g}, @sugar for the sauce{1%tsp} and @water for the sauce{100%ml} into the bacon. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to low. Simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}, then remove from the heat. Add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once the pasta is cooked, add to your sauce with the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Toss to coat, then season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Add a splash of @water{} if it's a little too thick. Warm through until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Share the chicken and bacon penne between your #bowls{}. Finish with a drizzle of the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}. Enjoy!